text: Miah Grace Madden (born April 9, 2002) is an Australian actress. She is known for her roles in The Unlisted (2019), the 10 Shake series Dive Club (2021), and the Network 10 and Paramount+ series Paper Dolls (2023). == Early life == Madden was born in Sydney, New South Wales. Her late father, Lee Madden, was an actor, activist and a poet. He died in a fatal car crash when she was only 2 years old. She is the younger half-sister of Madeleine Madden. She also has another younger sister named Ruby. == Career == Madden began her career as a child actress in 2012. Her early roles were in the movie The Sapphires (2012) and the ABC series The Gods of Wheat Street (2014). In 2021, she starred in Diva Club, a Netflix teen drama. ==References== ==Other websites== * Category:2002 births Category:Living people Category:Australian movie actors Category:Australian television actors Category:Actors from Sydney Category:Australian child actors Category:Australian television presenters
